This paper proposes a framework for learning category-specific 3D keypoints and their detectors for downstream tasks, specifically 3D pose estimation. The paper focuses on computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV and cs.RO sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a differentiable objective, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a neural network architecture, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric reasoning, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GR sub-category.
